text: Daphnella pulchra is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Raphitomidae.M.A. Peyrot, 1931-1932, Conchologie néogénique de l'Aquitaine, t. VI. (Actes Soc. Linn. Bordeaux, t. LXXXIILXXXIV, 1931-1932) ==Description== The length of the shell attains 13 mm. ==Distribution== Fossils of this marine species were found in Miocene strata in Aquitaine, France. ==References== pulchra Category:Gastropods described in 1932
title: Daphnella pulchra
